The paper focuses on learning motion patterns in videos using a fully convolutional network, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves learning entirely from synthetic video sequences, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of an objectness map and a conditional random field, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO). Overall, the paper's focus on computer vision and machine learning make cs.CV and cs.LG the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.RO.
